    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>Your bones, flesh, and skin are a bit more elastic than those of most goblins,when you fall, you tend to bounce a little better as a result.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p>Goblin</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<p>Whenever you take falling damage, the first 1d6 points of lethal damage suffered in the fall are automatically converted to nonlethal damage. You also gain a +2 trait bonus on all Reflex saves made to avoid unexpected falls.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Pathfinder Society</strong></p>\n<p>Only legal goblin PCs are allowed to take this trait.</p>",
